<HEADLINE> Netherlands Beat Argentina to Advance </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
MARSEILLE, July 4 (Xinhua) -- The Netherlands beat Argentina 2-1
to advance into the semi-finals of the World Cup finals on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The quarter-final match was full of action and the Netherlands
proved that they were the better side.
</P>
<P>
The Dutch team dominated the first half and opened the scoring at
the 12th minute through Patrick Kluivert who chipped home a header
pass from fellow striker Dennis Bergkamp.
</P>
<P>
They continued to enjoy a great advantage after the goal but
only 6 minutes later, the Argentine team beat a Dutch off-side trap
and levelled the score through Claudio Lopez.
</P>
<P>
The Dutch could have take the lead at the 5th minute but Wim
Jonk's shot hit the bar.
</P>
<P>
The Argentine team's counter-attack was quite effective and
playmaker Ariel Ortega also hit the bar at the 38th minute.
</P>
<P>
The Netherlands started the second half strongly and for nearly
15 minutes they didn't even give the Argentine team a single chance.
</P>
<P>
But at the 64th minute, the Argentine team finally launched
their first attack of the second half and Batistuta's shot hit the
bar again.
</P>
<P>
The Dutch team played more cautiously after the scare but they
suffered another blow at the 76th minute when Arthur Numan was sent
off for his second booking in the match.
</P>
<P>
The Argentine team took advantage that and assumed an upper hand
over their Dutch opponents. But Ortega made a unforgivable mistake
as he hit the Dutch goal-keeper Edwin van der Sar with his head and
was also shown the red card at the 87th minute.
</P>
<P>
Only two minutes after Ortega's send-off, the Dutch team dealt
their Argentine rivals a final blow when Bergkamp connected a
30-meter pass and beat the Argentine goal-keeper Carlos Roa to put
his team into the semi-finals.
</P>
<P>
The Dutch team will face title-holders Brazil in the semi-finals
while hosts France will take on the winners of the match between
Germany and Croatia to be played later on Saturday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
