<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Interest Rates Hit Price Of Homes In Britain </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, July 4 (Xinhua) -- The rise in interest rates is now
affecting the housing market in Britain, according to a new report
released here Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Home owners have been put off moving house and first-time
buyers are reluctant to commit themselves to a mortgage, the
report by ICM Housing Monitor said.
</P>
<P>
As a result, the earlier growth in house prices has ground to a
halt, it added.
</P>
<P>
"Interest rate rises have meant that people are now thinking
not just once or twice but three times before moving," said Paul
Raymond, managing director of Woolwich Property Services.
</P>
<P>
A spokesman for the Halifax, one of the largest Building
societies in Britain, said "Interest rate rises have affected
buyers' confidence."
</P>
<P>
"People are almost watching and waiting to see what happens to
interest rates, but we are expecting maybe only one more small
rise," he added.
</P>
<P>
The Bank of Engloand's monetary policy committee will make a
decision on interest rates next week when it meets to discuss the
economic situation now in Britain.
</P>
<P>
Observers in the housing market said that many estate agents
are pessimistic about a recovery in the market.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
