<DOCNO> XIE19980705.0017 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-07-04 17:29 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Yemeni Parliament Speaker Visits Iran </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, July 4 (Xinhua) -- Yemeni Parliament Speaker Sheikh
Abdullah Bin Hussein al-Ahmar arrived here Saturday afternoon for
a six-day official visit, the first one by a Yemeni parliament
speaker to Tehran since the 1979 Islamic revolution.
</P>
<P>
Upon his arrival, he said that his visit to Iran would help
promote the bilateral ties, especially the relations between the
two parliaments, the official Iranian news agency IRNA reported.
</P>
<P>
Iranian Majlis (Parliament) Speaker Ali Akbar Nateq-Nouri, who
greeted al-Ahmar at the airport, said that inter-parliamentary
exchanges would consolidate the bilateral ties and accelerate the
implementation of agreements reached between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
Besides holding talks with Nouri, al-Ahmar is scheduled to
meet with Iranian President Mohammad Khatami and Chairman of the
State Expediency Council Akbar Hashemi Rafsanjani on bilateral
ties and issues of common concern.
</P>
<P>
As a close ally of Yemeni President Ali Abdullah Saleh,
al-Ahmar is one of the most influential figures in the country. He
has been the Yemeni parliament speaker for seven years. 
</P>
