<HEADLINE> Tanzania Loses 2,584 Lives to Cholera in 11 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, July 4 (Xinhua) - A total of 2,584 Tanzanians
have died of cholera from last July 1 to May 31 this year, the
Minister for Health has said.
</P>
<P>
Aaron Chiduo said Friday at the parliament which is in session
for debating the 1998/99 budget in central city of Dodoma that
the deadly disease affected all the 20 regions in the mainland,
media here reported Saturday.
</P>
<P>
He said that among the 43,231 patients, there are 10,832 in
Mtwara, 6,741 in Dar es Salaam, 5,876 in Lindi, 3,414 in
Morogoro, 2,821 in Mara, 2,149 in Iringa, 1,956 in Kigoma and
1,444 in Coast.
</P>
<P>
He urged the public to keep their surroundings clean as one
way to fight cholera.
</P>
<P>
The minister said that another kind of disease, tuberculosis,
also affected the people heavily as its patients have increased
from 43,869 in 1996 to 44,477 last year due to squalid
environment and population pressure.
</P>
<P>
Chiduo requested the parliament to approve 29 billion
Shillings (43.6 million U.S. Dollars) for recurrent expenditure
and 21.5 billion Shillings for development expenditure in the
health sector which takes care of a total population of some 30
million. 
</P>
