<HEADLINE> Ugandans Urged to Fight Polio </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, July 4 (Xinhua) -- Uganda's Ministry of Health has
appealed to all Ugandans for active participation in the next
round of national polio immunization scheduled for August 2 to 3.
</P>
<P>
The appeal was made by Rotarian Sam Nsaramba, director of
health services in charge of operations, at a one-day national
immunization workshop here Saturday.
</P>
<P>
He urged health workers, Rotarians, teachers, church and
traditional leaders to embark on a serious campaign to ensure all
the children in the country could be taken for immunization
against polio before August 2.
</P>
<P>
The media was particularly urged to send the correct message
out to the general public so that no Ugandan child will ever
suffer from the disease.
</P>
<P>
Chairman of National Immunization Program John Barenzi, who is
also initiator of the polio immunization campaign, said the
repeating of the exercise is intended to boost the health
conditions for all the children.
</P>
<P>
The immunity against polio in children should be constantly
boosted to ensure of no chances for recurrence, he added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
