<HEADLINE> Croatia Lead Germany 1-0 at Halftime </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
LYON, July 4 (Xinhua) -- Croatia took a 1-0 lead over Germany in
the injury time of th first half as Robert Jarni beat Andreas
Kopke with a fierce long-range shot.
</P>
<P>
The German team dominated for most of the first half, but their
defender Christian Worns was shown the red card after he fouled
Croatian striker Davor Suker at the 40th minute.
</P>
<P>
Croatia immediately stepped up their attack and when the match
went into injury time, Jarni found himself unmarked with the ball in
front of the penalty area and he fired a shot to beat the German
goal-keeper.
</P>
<P>
The first half was full of fouls and besides Worns' red card,
two players from each team have been booked. 
</P>
</TEXT>
