<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Maldini Defends Usage of Del Piero </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, July 4 (Xinhua) -- Italian coach Cesare Maldini on Saturday
defended his choice of Alessandro Del Piero as starter in their loss
to France.
</P>
<P>
Maldini, who would be heading home with Squadra Azzura late
Saturday, told a news conference in Senlis north of Paris that it was
wrong to criticize the choice.
</P>
<P>
"If people regret the choices I made, like using Alessandro Del
Piero as a starter, that's a shame," Maldini said of Friday's
quarterfinal.
</P>
<P>
Maldini said: "Del Piero was well prepared physically. He was also
very motivated but perhaps lacked confidence."
</P>
<P>
The coach thought the Italian defence had performed a great job as
usual but lamented the failure to exalt in the penalty shoot-outs
which France won 4-3.
</P>
<P>
"We weren't thrashed, our goalkeeper had few saves to make... We
had the advantage during the shoot-outs but we did not know how to use
it," he said.
</P>
<P>
He said, "We've paid a dear price for it, but that's the law of
football."
</P>
<P>
Maldini hoped his son Paolo, who captained the team, would not
leave the squad following the loss.
</P>
<P>
He also vowed to come back four years later in the next finals to
be co-hosted by Japan and South Korea, if he was still the coach.
</P>
<P>
"Winning the World Cup was dream for us... I may have made
mistakes, but I will keep them to myself." 
</P>
</TEXT>
