<HEADLINE> Counting Days for World Horticulture Fair </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUNMING, July 5 (Xinhua) -- China Central Television (CCTV)
began a countdown today of the days left for '99 Kunming World
Horticulture Fair, 300 days away on May 1, in its daily prime time
weather report.
</P>
<P>
Officials say that the fair is the first to be held by the
Chinese government and is the largest international gala to
be held in China this century.
</P>
<P>
Nearly 60 countries, 30 international organizations, and
representatives of various provinces, municipalities and
autonomous regions in China are expected to take part.
</P>
<P>
Authorities in Yunnan Province, where the fair will be held,
held a video conference urging people all over the province to
help support the fair.
</P>
<P>
Yunnan's governor, Li Jiating, says, "We must ensure the
success of the fair by making careful preparations in all ways."
</P>
</TEXT>
