<HEADLINE> URGENT: Last Flight Lands at Kai Tak </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, July 5 (Xinhua) -- The last incoming flight landed
at Kai Tak at 11:40 p.m. Sunday, the last operational day of the
airport.
</P>
<P>
It was a Dragon Air flight from Chongqing, a southwest Chinese
city.
</P>
<P>
Around 1:00 a.m. Monday, there will be a lights out ceremony
putting an end to Kai Tak's 73 years of services. 
</P>
