<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Three-One Division in Semifinals Fourth Straight Time </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, July 5 (Xinhua) -- Three European teams and one South
American side occupy the World Cup semifinals berth as history repeats
itself for another time.
</P>
<P>
It is the fourth consecutive time that the semifinalists are
divided this way, but in the whole World Cup history it is the eighth
time.
</P>
<P>
There are only three times that the semifinalists were all
European, the last time in 1982.
</P>
<P>
The host countries have a quite high chance to reach the last four,
with 10 out of 16 successful.
</P>
<P>
The hosts which failed to reach the semifinals were France in 1938,
Switzerland in 1954, Mexico in 1970 and 1986, Spain in 1982, the
United States in 1994. 
</P>
</TEXT>
