<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Beijing's High-Tech Firms Report Hefty Export Growth </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 5 (Xinhua) -- High-tech enterprises in the
Chinese capital reported an export volume of 11.3 million U.S.
dollars in the first five months, a surge of 46 percent from the
same period last year.
</P>
<P>
The high-tech enterprises -- which often deal in research,
product development and trade at the same time -- also imported
goods valued at 5.68 million U.S. dollars in the January-May
period, 2.5 times the comparable figure of last year.
</P>
<P>
This year Beijing's high-tech firms have increased efforts to
develop new products to counter the effects of the Asian financial
crisis, which has persisted since last July.
</P>
<P>
The Beijing Three-Ring New Materials and High-Tech Company, whose
annual exports average nearly 10 million U.S. dollars, saw its
exports grow 15.6 percent on a yearly basis to 4.16 million U.S.
dollars in the January-May period.
</P>
<P>
This year developed countries and regions have continued to be
the major export markets of Beijing's high-tech enterprises, whose
exports to the United States totalled 3.49 million U.S. dollars in
the first five months. Exports to Europe came to 2.76 million
U.S. dollars during the period.
</P>
<P>
High-tech enterprises in the Chinese capital have beefed up
their efforts to tap new markets in Hong Kong, Taiwan, countries
of the Association of Southeast Asian Nations (ASEAN), and Africa.
</P>
<P>
Exports to ASEAN countries, for example, totaled 750,000 U.S.
dollars in the first five months, a surge of 87.5 percent from a
year ago. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
