<DOCNO> XIE19980705.0068 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-07-05 14:30 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> French Defense Minister Visits Saudi Arabia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY, July 5 (Xinhua) -- French Defense Minister Alain
Richard Sunday arrived in the Saudi Red Sea city of Jeddah in a
bid to win arms deals, Kuwait News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
French Ambassador to Saudi Arabia Hubert de la Fortelle told
the news agency that Richard will hold talks with his Saudi
counterpart Prince Sultan Ibn Abdul-Aziz on defense, security and
political issues.
</P>
<P>
The ambassador said the talks will cover bilateral defense
cooperation and a potential Saudi purchase of French-made Le Clair
main battle tanks, a deal facing competition from the United
States and Britain.
</P>
<P>
France hopes to sell 350 Le Clair tanks and 38 recovery
vehicles worth 3 billion U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
The ambassador said France is confident it will win the deal,
especially after the Saudi armed forces conducted tests on the
French tanks in its desert and asked for modifications to the
engine to adapt to the demanding environment.
</P>
<P>
According to the French diplomat, France is also hoping to
sell the kingdom Rafale warplanes, which Paris believes are the
most sophisticated warplanes of the 21st century.
</P>
<P>
In addition to defense cooperation, Richard and Prince Sultan
will review regional issues, including the deadlocked Middle East
peace process, the French ambassador said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
