<HEADLINE> NPC Chairman Meets With Mexico's Foreign Secretary </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 5 (Xinhua) -- Li Peng, chairman of China's
National People's Congress (NPC) Standing Committee, in a meeting
with Mexico's Secretary of Foreign Relations Rosario Green Macias
here this afternoon, spoke highly of Mexico's success in economic
and social development in recent years.
</P>
<P>
Li recalled his visit to Mexico in 1995, adding that both
Mexico and China are both important developing countries with a
long history of friendship. Li said that closer cooperation
between the two is in the basic interest of their peoples and
helpful to peace and development in the whole world.
</P>
<P>
The NPC and Mexico's parliament have maintained friendly
contacts and bilateral relations have continued to develop, he
said, and frequent communication between the two parliaments and
committees has played an important role in developing the
friendship and cooperative ties between the two.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese hope that the NPC and Mexican parliament will
continue their close relations to make a new contribution to
bilateral friendship and cooperative ties.
</P>
<P>
The Mexican Secretary said that Mexico places great importance
on developing relations with China and hopes to enhance
cooperation with China in politics, the economy, and culture.
</P>
<P>
At the request of the guest, Li also briefed the Mexican
Foreign Secretary China's National People's Congress system and
the legislative procedures of the NPC. Ding Shisun, vice-chairman
of NPC Standing Committee was present at the meeting.  
</P>
