<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 5 (Xinhua) -- Li Peng, chairman of the Standing
Committee of China's National People's Congress (NPC), in a
meeting with the Greek Parliament President Apostolos Kaklamanis
today, said that the NPC values relations with the Greek
Parliament and thinks that strengthening contacts could increase
mutual understanding and friendship.
</P>
<P>
Li said that parliamentary exchanges are an important part of
bilateral relations and that he is convinced that this visit will
play a positive role in the development of the friendship and
cooperation between the two countries and the two parliaments.
</P>
<P>
Li said that China and Greece are friends and that bilateral
relations have developed smoothly since diplomatic ties were
opened in 1972, and the two countries have had good cooperation in
international affairs, and that he hopes to further cooperation
and consultation in the future.
</P>
<P>
Li said that Sino-Greek long-term, stable friendship and
cooperation are in the two countries' interest and conducive to
building a new partnership between Asia and Europe.
