<HEADLINE> New Sample Stocks For Shanghai Index </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, July 5 (Xinhua) -- The Shanghai Stock Exchange will
replace 15 less qualified sample stocks with 15 more qualified
ones to its SSR-30 index starting tomorrow.
</P>
<P>
The SSR-30 started two years ago, based on 30 blue chips
selected from more than 400 A shares for domestic investors on the
Shanghai Stock Exchange.
</P>
<P>
Local officials say that the move will fit the new market
situation better and make the index more reliable.
</P>
<P>
The stock value of the new 30 blue chips is 5.73 billion yuan
(about 700 million US dollars), or 17.01 percent of the total
figure. 
</P>
