<HEADLINE> Chinese Houses of Detention And Better Administration </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JINAN, July 5 (Xinhua) -- Houses of detention in the city of
Jinan, the capital of China's Shandong Province, will enforce the
law better and have more civil management, according to a senior
Public Security Bureau officer in Jinan.
</P>
<P>
He says that houses of detention will protect inmates and keep
them safe from assaults, either from the staff or other inmates
and inmates are being assured of their basic living standards,
daily necessities, time for outdoor activities, and right to
appeal.
</P>
<P>
Staff members say they will be clean and honest and never ask
for or accept gifts from the inmates and their relatives, and that
those who violate these promises will be penalized.
</P>
<P>
Houses of detention also have plans to periodically invite
deputies to the city's People's Congress and members of the city's
Committee of the Chinese People's Political Consultative
Conference to inspect the houses.
</P>
<P>
The senior officer said that any individual can file an appeal
with disciplinary inspection departments any time he or she finds
that the house of detention is not acting in accordance with
this. 
</P>
</TEXT>
