<HEADLINE> Flooding on Middle Reaches Of Yangtze River </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANCHANG, July 5 (Xinhua) -- Efforts are underway to repair a
section along the middle reaches of the Yangtze River, where the
water has gone over its banks as a result of continuous heavy
rains.
</P>
<P>
The water level at a 12-km section near the city of Jiujiang
in east China's Jiangxi Province has reached record highs,
according to city flood control headquarters.
</P>
<P>
It is threatening 82 state enterprises, 110,000 ha of arable
land, several major railways lines, and half of the city's people,
an official from the headquarters said.
</P>
<P>
Liu Jifu, the city's acting mayor, says that they are
determined to protect the banks at any cost, and that government
departments have spent more than 60 million yuan on flood work. So
far, no water has gone over important sections of the bank and
local people have all been moved to safe areas, he says.
</P>
<P>
The central government has dispatched experts to direct the
flood work in the city, which is the hub for east China. 
</P>
</TEXT>
