<HEADLINE> Chinese University Students Volunteer To Work in Countryside </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 5 (Xinhua) -- A ceremony was held today at
Beijing University to mark the beginning of a program where
university students are being to volunteer to work in rural areas
during their summer holidays.
</P>
<P>
The activity is being sponsored by the Ministry of Education
and government organizations to get 500,000 university students
from across China to go to rural areas this summer to help provide
people with various cultural, scientific, and health services.
</P>
<P>
As many as 200 volunteers attended today's ceremony, where
Zhang Tianbao, vice-minister of education, and other officials
presented the volunteers with books on practical farming
techniques. One team of eight Beijing University graduate students
has already left for rural parts of Heilongjiang Province in the
Northeast.
</P>
<P>
The activity is also intended to give college students a
greater understanding of the country's basic situation and to
encourage them to make a greater contribution to rural regions,
explains Hu Chunhua, a member of the Secretariat of the Central
Committee of the Communist Youth League of China. 
</P>
</TEXT>
