<HEADLINE> Hoddle Not Yet Ready to Discuss Future </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
PARIS, July 5 (Xinhua) -- England team manager Glenn Hoddle said
he was not yet ready to discuss a new contract with the Football
Association (FA).
</P>
<P>
FA chairman Keith Wiseman had offered to talk with Hoddle about
extending his contract, which is due to end after the 2000 European
Champinship.
</P>
<P>
But Hoddle said he would not commit to anything:The next World
Cup is too far away for me to consider at the moment."
</P>
<P>
"There is a lot of water to pass under the bridge before then. I
want to keep my options open," said Hoddle, "Both the FA and myself
are aware that my contract runs until Euro 2000."
</P>
<P>
Hoddle said:"I don't see any reason for them or me to change the
situation. If the agreement was coming to an end then it would be
different." 
</P>
