<HEADLINE> Shearer Says To Change for Owen </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
PARIS, July 5 (Xinhua) -- England striker Alan Shearer said it's
time to change his game to ensure England get the best out of young
forward Mchael Owen.
</P>
<P>
Owen became the hero of the World Cup finals with his splendid
performance despite England's elimination at the quarter-finals.
</P>
<P>
Shearer said:"When you have two center-forwards like Michael and
me it's obvious we can't both play the same way."
</P>
<P>
"With his pace and finishing skills, it makes sense to use
Michael where he can cause most damage because he frightens
defenders to death," Shearer said. 
</P>
