<DATE_TIME> 1998-07-05 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Edition Of Pearl Buck's Works Published </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANJING, July 5 (Xinhua) -- The "Selected Works of Pearl Buck"
and "The Autobiography of Pearl Buck" have recently been released
in China in commemoration of the American writer.
</P>
<P>
Pearl Buck spent 34 years of her life in China from infancy on
and wrote many novels based on her Chinese experiences, one of
which won her the Nobel Prize for Literature in 1934. Her novels
have been translated into more than 100 languages.
</P>
<P>
The recently published works were the product of Nanjing
University, where Buck taught English for 12 years, and the
Lijiang Publishing House.
</P>
<P>
Liu Haiping, a professor at Nanjing University, says that
Buck's novels about Chinese society in the 1930s and 1940s can
give Westerners a better understanding of the Chinese people and
their culture.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980705.0092 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-07-05 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 2,400-year-old Tomb Excavated in Zhejiang Province </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, July 5 (Xinhua) -- A tomb on a mountaintop believed
to belong to a ruler of the Yue State in the late Spring and
Autumn Period (770-476 BC) has been excavated in Shaoxing, east
China's Zhejiang Province.
</P>
<P>
The tomb, covering an area of 100,000 square meters, was built
in a pit that was dug in Yinshan Mountain. In the 32-meter-long
burial room was a wooden coffin made of a whole trunk that is six
meters long and one meter in diameter.
</P>
<P>
The burial room, made of painted wood, was wrapped with more
than 140 layers of bark. Above the bark was a one-meter-thick
layer of charcoal. The whole pit was sealed with black clay.
</P>
<P>
Although the tomb had been robbed before, Chinese archeologists
unearthed pieces of jade, lacquer, bronzeware and stoneware.
</P>
<P>
The archeologists, who have found no written records in the
tomb, believe it belonged to King Yun Chang of the Yue State,
father of King Gou Jian.
</P>
<P>
Gou Jian is the most famous king in the history of the Yue
State which conquered the much stronger Wu State.
</P>
<P>
The city of Shaoxing is planning to build a museum at the
site. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
