<HEADLINE> Argentine Coach Quits After Elimination </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
PARIS, July 5 (Xinhua) -- Argentine coach Daniel Passarella
resigned after his team's 2-1 loss to the Netherlands at the World
Cup finals on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Passarella admitted he had fallen short of his own standards:"I
didn't achieve my goal of getting us into the last four of the
competition."
</P>
<P>
"We played a good tournament against the best teams in the
world, but sometimes it doesn't go for you," said Passarella.
</P>
<P>
Passarella, who captained the Argentine team from 1976 to 1982,
took over as coach from Alfio Basile after Argentina's second round
defeat in the 1994 World Cup. 
</P>
