<HEADLINE> Senior Chinese Party Official Visits Singapore </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, July 5 (Xinhua) -- A delegation of the Communist
Party of China (CPC), led by Huang Ju, member of the Political
Bureau of the CPC Central Committee and Secretary of the CPC
Municipal Committee of Shanghai, arrived here Sunday for a
five-day goodwill visit to Singapore.
</P>
<P>
Huang came at the invitation of Singapore Deputy Prime Minister
Lee Hsien Loong.
</P>
<P>
Singapore is the first leg of Huang Ju's four-nation tour which
will also take him to South Africa, Zimbabwe, and Mauritius.
Huang's current visit to Singapore is his first tour of the city
state.
</P>
<P>
In a written speech upon arrival at the airport, Huang said the
traditional friendship between the peoples of China and Singapore
is a long-standing one.
</P>
<P>
The friendly relations between China and Singapore have
witnessed smooth and all-round development especially since the
establishment of diplomatic ties, he said.
</P>
<P>
He expressed the hope and belief that his visit would
contribute to the further enhancement of understanding and
friendship between the two peoples, and to the development of
relations between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
During his stay here, Huang Ju will call on Singapore Prime
Minister Goh Chok Tong, Senior Minister Lee Kuan Yew, deputy prime
minister Lee Hsien Loong and Minister for Law &AMP; Foreign Affairs S.
Jayakumar, and his itinerary also includes visits to a number of
Statutory Boards and Government-linked companies as well as a
community center.
</P>
<P>
Shortly after their arrival, Huang and his delegation visited
the Bishan Community Center, a community organization designed to
promote community harmony and serve as a bridge between the
government and the residents.
</P>
<P>
The Singapore People's Association leaders briefed Huang on the
history, functions and activities of the community organizations
in Singapore. 
</P>
