<DOCNO> XIE19980705.0103 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-07-05 11:52 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Iranian Speaker Rules out Dissolution of </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, July 5 (Xinhua) -- Iran's conservative Majlis
(Parliament) Speaker Nateq Nouri Sunday ruled out the dissolution
of the Majlis, saying no one or authority has the right to do so.
</P>
<P>
This was the strongest reaction of the county's conservatives
to the recent call by pro-moderate university students for
dissolving the Majlis, which they called as a puppet parliament.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at the Majlis' open session, Nouri said the Majlis has
a legal and important place in the Islamic system and is "the
symbol of the system's independence and republicanism."
</P>
<P>
Nouri expressed indignation at those who launched insults
against Majlis deputies and called for dissolving the
parliament. Such call was the first since the foundation of the
Islamic Republic of Iran in 1979.
</P>
<P>
At a gathering at Tehran University in support of former
Interior Minister Abdollah Nouri, a representative of the
moderates impeached by the Majlis last month, thousands of
students denounced the Majlis' move and calling for its
dissolution.
</P>
<P>
The students chanted slogans: "We do not want a puppet Majlis,
We do not want Nateq Nouri"
</P>
<P>
The Iranian Majlis speaker described the students' call as an
"alarm bell" for the country, warning that foreigners might have
had a hand in the issue. "Otherwise, why has BBC (British
Broadcasting Corporation) made interviews about the Majlis'
dissolution and even gave suggestions about certain issues?" he
asked.
</P>
<P>
Nouri said that weakening the Majlis would weaken the
government, because a legitimate government should obtain vote of
confidence from the Majlis while a "puppet Majlis will establish
a puppet government."
</P>
<P>
He stressed that under the constitution, no one can dissolve
the Majlis, adding that supreme leader Ayatollah Ali Khamenei also
rejected such a proposal "with insight and respect to the people's
will." 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
