<HEADLINE> Shanghai Plans Forest Tourism Festival </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, July 5 (Xinhua) -- This largest economic and
financial center of China will launch a forest tourism festival
during the Oct. 1 National Day holiday season.
</P>
<P>
The First Chongming Forest Tourism Festival will be held on
Chongming Island of Shanghai's suburban Chongming County. The
island is China's third largest and has a national forest park of
more than 330 hectares.
</P>
<P>
Considered a paradise for birds, the island is home to more
than three million migrating birds of more than 100 types.
</P>
<P>
Besides hunting and traditional-type entertainment, there will
also be cliff climbing and other challenging sports activities
during the festival, said Gu Guolin, magistrate of Chongming
County.
</P>
<P>
Currently, a cliff wall of more than 20 meters is being
constructed, he said.
</P>
<P>
During the festival, 220,000 urban people who were sent to work
in the countryside of Chongming 30 years ago will be invited back
to see the great changes taken place on the island.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
