<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Overseas Investment in Guiyang Rising Steadily </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUIYANG, July 5 (Xinhua) -- Overseas investment in this capital
of southwest China's Guizhou Province, one of the country's most
underdeveloped areas, has increased steadily in recent years.
</P>
<P>
Guiyang had approved more than 870 overseas-funded enterprises
by the end of last year, with the value of overseas investment
actually utilized totaling 175 million U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
In the first five months of this year, another 21
overseas-funded projects were approved with contracted overseas
investment hitting 45.7 million U.S. dollars, 75 percent and 240
percent more than the comparable figures of last year,
respectively.
</P>
<P>
A municipal official in overseas economic and trade relations
said that investors from Hong Kong, Macao, Taiwan and countries in
southeast Asia accounted for 77 percent of all overseas investment
in Guiyang. Companies from Europe and North America accounted for
another 17 percent.
</P>
<P>
Overseas investment in Guiyang covers such sectors as
agriculture, forestry, animal husbandry, fisheries, water
conservancy, industry, construction, transportation, real estate,
catering, public facilities, health, sports and consultancy
business, the official said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
