<HEADLINE> Middle School Students to Launch Film Festival </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, July 5 (Xinhua) -- Middle-school students in this
capital of south China's prospering Guangdong Province will hold a
film festival of their own between July 11 and Aug. 30 this year.
</P>
<P>
The First Guangzhou Middle School Student Film Festival is
believed to be the first-ever film festival initiated and
organized by middle-school students. The festival executive
committee consists of more than 20 middle-school students, who
will independently deal with issues relating to the festival.
</P>
<P>
Ten Chinese and overseas films, including "The Flower Season
and Rainy Season" and "Jane Eyre," will be shown during the
festival, which will feature patriotism and collectivism.
</P>
<P>
All middle-school students in Guangzhou will only have to show
a special card issued by the student federation and pay three yuan
to watch the films.  
</P>
