<HEADLINE> Hong Kong Companies Invest More In Zhangzhou </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FUZHOU, July 5 (Xinhua) -- Companies from Hong Kong have
steadily increased their investment in Zhangzhou, a coastal city
in east China's Fujian Province.
</P>
<P>
Zhangzhou approved 96 Hong Kong-funded enterprises in the first
five months of this year, with contracted investment totaling 180
million U.S. dollars. Both figures were 57 percent of the total
for the five-month period and nearly double the comparable figures
of last year.
</P>
<P>
This is a result of Zhangzhou's increased effort to attract
investors from Hong Kong since it returned to the motherland last
July, a city official said.
</P>
<P>
Over the past year Zhangzhou has also taken effective measures
to improve its overall investment environment, he added.
</P>
<P>
Companies from Hong Kong have invested in agriculture,
forestry, processing trade, plastics, real estate, VCDs and other
areas, according to the official.
</P>
<P>
Though affected by the Asian financial crisis, Zhangzhou's
exports to Hong Kong continued to rise this year. The export
volume reached 200 million U.S. dollars in the first five months
of this year, about two-thirds of Zhangzhou's total exports during
the period. 
</P>
