<HEADLINE> Orangemen Begin Controversial Parade in Portadown </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
LONDON, July 5 (Xinhua) -- Five thousand Orangemen marched out
of Portadown on their way to the annual church service at Drumcree.
</P>
<P>
It is feared the controversial parade may spark violence and
damage the Northern Ireland peace agreement.
</P>
<P>
Under pressure from the Roman Catholics in the parade area, the
independent Parades Commission has decided to ban the Protestant
march on the traditional route that include the Catholic areas in
Portadown, southwest of provincial capital Belfast.
</P>
<P>
Orange leaders appealed their marchers for calm, but insisted
they would defy the ban and march back from the church along the
mainly nationalist Gargaghy Road.
</P>
<P>
Up to 2,000 troops and police are on standby in case the
Orangemen attempt to break the block.
</P>
<P>
In the past two years, the parade has sparked violence between
Orangemen and police. 
