<HEADLINE> Mexican Referee Carter Flashes Most Sendings-Off </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, July 5 (Xinhua) -- Mexican referee Arturo Brizio Carter has
set a new record for sendings-off after officiating Saturday's World
Cup quarterfinal between Argentia and the Netherlands.
</P>
<P>
Carter, a 42-year-old lawyer, has sent off seven players in six
World Cup finals games so far, including those at last edition in the
United States in 1994.
</P>
<P>
His record surpassed that of French referee Joel Quiniou, who
collected five sendings-off in eight games, FIFA spokesman Keith
Cooper said on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
At this World Cup, he had given the marching order to French
playmaker Zinadine Zidane and Saudi Arabia's Mohammed Al-Khilaiwi in a
group C games.
</P>
<P>
On Saturday he sent off Arthur Numan of the Netherlands and
Argentina's Ariel Ortega. 
</P>
