<HEADLINE> Kazakh Officials Hail Jiang's Successful Visit </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ALMA-ATA, July 4 (Xinhua) -- Kazakh officials said Saturday
that Chinese President Jiang Zemin's successful visit to
Kazakhstan has contributed greatly to the development of the
relations between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
In an interview with Xinhua, Presidential Press Secretary Kairat
Sarybaev said Jiang's just-concluded visit has injected new
vitality into the Kazakhstan-China relationship.
</P>
<P>
He noted that the good personal relations between Jiang and
Kazakh President Nursultan Nazarbayev will play a positive role in
furthering bilateral ties.
</P>
<P>
Mubtar Abliazov, minister of energy, industry and trade, said
the visit has achieved positive results. With the leaders of the
two countries sharing views on many issues, he said, the economic
relations between the two countries will see a period of fast
growth.
</P>
<P>
Nurlan Kapparov, president of the state-owned oil company
Kazakhoil, said that cooperation in the oil sector will benefit
from Jiang's visit because the two leaders agreed to strengthen
cooperation in energy, especially in the oil sector.
</P>
<P>
Deputy Foreign Minister Askar Shakirov said that the fact that
Jiang visited Kazakhstan twice in two years demonstrates that
bilateral relations have grown to a new level.
</P>
<P>
All these Kazakh officials believed that the most important
achievement of Jiang's visit is the signing of a supplementary
agreement on border issues.
</P>
<P>
The agreement has completely solved all the remaining border
issues between the two countries, turning the border into a bond
of friendship and laying a solid foundation for the future
development of bilateral relations, they said. 
</P>
