</P>
<P>
MOSCOW -- Russia will cut the export quotas of four Russian oil
companies by one third over the third quarter of this year, the
Interfax news agency reported on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The four companies are Onako, Sidanko (a Varyeganneft
subsidiary), Tatneft and Bashneft.
</P>
<P>
The report said Russia will export 28.2 million tons of oil in
the third quarter.
</P>
<P>
Russia has agreed to cut its oil production and exports to join
the efforts of the Organization of the Petroleum Exporting
Countries (OPEC) to boost oil prices on the world market.
(Russia-Oil-Export-Cut)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
SEOUL -- The South Korean government and business conglomerates
Saturday agreed to increase the country's exports to overcome the
current financial crisis.
</P>
<P>
The nine-point agreement was published after South Korean
President Kim Dae-jung met tycoons of the groupings on Saturday
afternoon.
</P>
<P>
Under the agreement, the government will complete the
restructuring of the ailing financial sector as soon as possible
to stabilize the nation's financial system, while the business
groups will work hard to restructure their operations and
management to survive the market system. (SKorea-Exports) 
</P>
