<HEADLINE> 11 Tamil Rebels Killed in Northern Sri Lanka </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, July 5 (Xinhua) -- At least 11 Tamil rebels were
killed in separate places fighting in Northern province Saturday,
Military spokesman Ink Dewage said Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Dewage said that fighting started at around 11:25 a.m. Saturday
in northwest of Olumadu. Government troops ambushed and killed at
least three rebels who were moving towards a rebel bunker.
</P>
<P>
Around 3:30 p.m. Saturday in the same place, government troops
engaged a group of Tamil rebels and killed four rebels.
</P>
<P>
In another incident around 12:00 p.m. in east of Mankulam town,
troops confronted a small group of rebels and engaged them with
small arms killing three terrorists, the spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
He added that government troops sniped and killed one rebel
around 3:45 p.m. the same day at Kilinochchci.
</P>
<P>
The Tamil rebels have been fighting against the government for
a separate state in the north and east of the island country since
1983. 
</P>
