<HEADLINE> hke - Milosevic Meets Russian Deputy FM on Kosovo Issue </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BELGRADE, July 5 (Xinhua) -- Yugoslav President Slobodan
Milosevic met Russian Deputy Foreign Minister Nikolai Afanasyevsky
here Saturday on ways to end the Kosovo crisis by political means.
</P>
<P>
The two sides, as reported by the Tanjug news agency, expressed
the belief that political dialogues between the Serbian government
and ethnic Albanians in Kosovo would find a solution to the
satisfaction of all ethnic groups there.
</P>
<P>
The Serbian government has agreed to talk with political
parties representing ethnic Albanians in Kosovo, a province of the
Serbian republic of Yugoslavia.
</P>
<P>
Afanasyevsky said Russia backs Yugoslavia and Serbia in their
efforts to peacefully resolve the Kosovo crisis and defuse the
intense situation there.
</P>
<P>
The Russian official was here to help Belgrade deliver its
commitment made in a joint statement issued by Milosevic and
Russian President Boris Yeltsin on June 16 in Moscow.
</P>
<P>
In the statement, Milosevic agreed to resume talks with ethnic
Albanians seeking independence from Belgrade but ruled out a total
withdrawal of Yugoslavia's military forces from Kosovo.
</P>
<P>
More than 300 people have been killed and thousands of others
forced to fleed their homes since February amid clashes between
Serbian security forces and armed Kosovo separatists. 
