<HEADLINE> Costa Rican Pineapple Exports Rise </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SAN JOSE, July 4 (Xinhua) -- Costa Rica is expected to export
over 8 million boxes, each weighing 18.8 kilograms, of Hawaiian
pineapple this year, the Commerce Ministry said Saturday.
</P>
<P>
With climate favorable for growing Hawaiian pineapple, this
Central American country began to export the produce three years
ago, and the volume amounted to 7.5 million boxes last year.
</P>
<P>
The pineapple variety earned 46.02 million U.S. dollars in
foreign exchanges during the first five months of the year, making
up 6 percent of the country's total farm exports in the period.
</P>
<P>
More than 60 percent of the Costa Rican pineapples go to the
U.S. market, 30 percent to European countries and the rest to
South American and Asian countries. 
