<HEADLINE> Kyrgyzstan: Wreckage of Russian Helicopter Found </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, July 4 (Xinhua) -- A search team found on Saturday the
wreckage of a Russian military helicopter that went down in
Kyrgyzstan last month and confirmed the death of all the 20 people
aboard.
</P>
<P>
As reported by Russia's Itar-Tass News Agency, the helicopter
lost contact with the ground 15 minutes before landing on June 25
near the mountainous Central Asian republic's border with China.
</P>
<P>
Aboard the copter, a Mi-8 of Kyrgyzstan-based Russian border
guards, were four Russian crew members and 16 Kyrgyz passengers.
</P>
<P>
Russian border guards started in 1992 to patrol along the
Sino-Kyrgyz border, which extends for more than 1,000 kilometers.
</P>
<P>
Russian-made Mi-8 helicopters were involved in several
accidents in recent weeks.
</P>
<P>
On Wednesday, three people, including a European Bank for
Reconstruction and Development worker, were killed and 13 injured
when an Mi-8 crashed on take-off near Lake Baikal in southeastern
Siberia.
</P>
<P>
Also Wednesday, three crew members were injured when a Mi-8 of
Tajikistan's elite presidential guard crashed and caught fire
while landing at an airport in Tajikobad, 260 kilometers east of
Dushanbe.
</P>
<P>
On June 1, three crew members and two scientists were killed
when a Mi-8 bound for the Russian Antarctic station of
Novolazarevskaya crashed onto the ice 15 minutes after taking off
from a research vessel. 
</P>
</TEXT>
