<HEADLINE> Antidrug Meeting to Be Held in Brazil </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRASILIA, July 4 (Xinhua) -- A meeting on the prevention of
drug use in workplace and family will be held on July 8-10 in
Porto Alegre, the capital of Rio Grande Do Sul.
</P>
<P>
The meeting is organized by the Brazilian state of Rio Grande
Do Sul and the United Nations International Drug Control Program,
an official source said Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Attending the meeting will be representatives of Argentina,
Brazil, Paraguay and Uruguay, the four member countries of the
Southern Common Market (Mercosur), and its associates Chile and
Bolivia.
</P>
<P>
The meeting, the first f its kind, aims at promoting the
implementation of the global drug prevention programs in the
region where drug addiction affects people every day.
</P>
<P>
Forty-four companies and schools in Rio Grande Do Sul are
undertaking a United Nations project against drug use in
workplaces and in families. 
</P>
</TEXT>
