<HEADLINE> Charlotte Sting Beat Phoenix Mercury 68-66 in WNBA </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, July 4 (Xinhua) -- Christy Smith netted her only
two points with 20 seconds left to push the Charlotte Sting a
68-66 victory over the Phoenix Mercury on Saturday in Charlotte.
</P>
<P>
The Eastern Conference leader Sting seemed as if they would be
beaten on their home floor early in the game, when the Mercuy shot
to a 18-7 lead through the first half.
</P>
<P>
But with a help of Andrea Stinson's 19 points, the Sting roared
bach to wrap up the first half 31-27.
</P>
<P>
Umeki Webb scored six points and twice put Phoenix ahead by two
points. But Stinson hit two jumpers in the final two minutes to
save Charlotte's fate.
</P>
<P>
Jennifer Gillom was the biggest gun for the Mercury with 21
points, and Webb added 15. Tracy Reid and Sharon Manning each
scored 14 for the Sting. 
</P>
