<HEADLINE> Thai Embassy, Consulates in China to Speed Up Visa </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, July 5 (Xinhua) -- The Thai Foreign Ministry is
thinking of buying 15 new electric certifier printers for the Thai
Embassy and three consulates in China to speed up visa issuance,
the Bangkok Post reported Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The Thai Embassy in Beijing and consulates in Shanghai and
Kunming would receive three new electric certifier printers each,
while the Thai Consulate in Guangzhou would get six, Kitti
Wasinondh, deputy Foreign Ministry spokesman, was quoted as
saying.
</P>
<P>
"The Foreign Ministry gives priority to China because there are
at least 1,500 Chinese applying daily for visas to visit Thailand.
But the old process is very slow and it takes three days to issue
a visa. The new printer will take just one day," Kitti said.
</P>
<P>
Records showed 239,228 people in Guangzhou applied for Thai
visas last year, 59,692 in Beijing, 73,014 in Kunming, 47,897 in
Shanghai. 
</P>
</TEXT>
