<HEADLINE> Eastern Europe Must Have Own Development Models, Declaration </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, July 4 (Xinhua) -- The central and eastern European
countries must come up with their own development models
fitting the economic, cultural, social and environmental context
of the region, said the final declaration issued Saturday at the
end of the Fifth European Economic Forum.
</P>
<P>
The document called on central government officials of the
countries in the country to closely cooperate with local
institutions to attract as mush foreign investment as possible by
capitalizing on all the existing economic potentials.
</P>
<P>
Cooperation among the central and eastern European countries
has been increasing.
</P>
<P>
The three-day forum, which started here on Thursday, was
organized by the European Local and Regional Powers Congress to
discuss policies of investments and regional development at
pan-European level.
</P>
<P>
The meeting was attended by about 400 officials from the 40
European Council member countries. 
</P>
