<HEADLINE> Menem Praises World Cup Team Performance </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUENOS AIRES, July 4 (Xinhua) -- Argentine President Carlos
Menem said today that the national football team played
excellently, even if it lost 2-1 to the Netherlands in the World
Cup finals.
</P>
<P>
Menem acknowledged that the Netherlands was a great team, but
maintained that the Argentine squad should have not lost, in what
was the first official reaction after the end of the game.
</P>
<P>
The Argentine public seemed to accept with stoicism the defeat,
despite the high hopes of reaching the semifinals.
</P>
<P>
There were no demonstrations or disturbances in this capital,
as those of June 30, when Argentina defeated the British team in
the second round.
</P>
<P>
The local authorities took measures before today's match to
prevent any incident if the national team would win.
</P>
<P>
However, in the middle of the rain and with many policemen
deployed in the main streets of downtown Buenos Aires, the
atmosphere of sadness could be felt.
</P>
<P>
Julio Grondona, the Argentine Football Association president,
said from Marseilles, France, that at least it was important that
the national team was ranked among the best eight of the world.
</P>
<P>
The Argentine football team starts its return Sunday to be here
on Monday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
