<HEADLINE> Passarella: Loss May Due to Stamina Problem </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MARSEILLE, July 4 (Xinhua) -- Argentina coach Daniel Alberto
Passarella said the lack of stamina might be one of the problems for
their loss to the Netherlands in the World Cup quarterfinals on
Saturday.
</P>
<P>
"There were two Argentina teams, one in the first half and one in
the second," he said. "I think that it is more a question of physical
condition than of ball control."
</P>
<P>
He added: "We did not completely recover after the extremely
intense match against England. Other than the fact that we had one
less day of rest than our adversary, it is natural that we confront
more difficult teams as we advance in the competition."
</P>
<P>
As to the foul that earned a red card for Arnaldo Ortega, he said:
"It was an unfortunate foul that I did not see clearly. I can't say
whether or not there was a penalty, but it deprived us of one of our
players and allowed the Dutch to score."
</P>
<P>
He added: "As I've already said many times, our objective was to be
among the top four teams. We were not able to accomplish this, but we
played very well anyway." 
</P>
</TEXT>
