<DATE_TIME> 1998-07-05 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Croatia Advance with 3-0 Victory </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
LYON, July 4 (Xinhua) -- Croatia scored a comfortable 3-0
victory over the aging German team in a quarter-final match here on
Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The German team started the match strongly and forced a corner
in their first attack. Dietmar Hamann and Oliver Bierhoff both had
scoring chances in the first half but Hamann headed the ball over
the crossbar while Bierhoff's header was saved by Croat goal-keeper
Drazen Ladic.
</P>
<P>
Christian Worns' send-off in the first half came as a turning
point for Croatia and they immediately fought forward to take over
the domination.
</P>
<P>
Robert Jarni opened the scoring for Croatia in the injury time
of the first half. They continued to explore the weakness of the
German team in the second half as Goran Vlaovic and Davor Suker each
added one to seal up the perfect victory.
</P>
<P>
Germany's top marksmen Jurgen Klinsmann and Oliver Bierhoff
failed to show their usual flair in front of a tough Croat defence
line.
</P>
<P>
Croatia, taking part in their first World Cup finals, will take
on hosts France in the semi-finals.
</P>
<P>
For the German team, it was the second stright time they were
beaten in the quarter-finals. In 1994, they were eliminated by
Bulgaria in the same stage of the tournament. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
