<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Argentina Lacks Concentration: Veron </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MARSEILLE, July 4 (Xinhua) -- Argentina's loss in the World Cup
quarterfinal against the Netherlands was partly due to their lack of
concentration, Argentine player Juan Veron said on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
"We could have put more pressure on the Netherlands team, but we
did not. Moreover, we lacked concentration," said Veron.
</P>
<P>
Veron refused to comment on the sending off of Ariel Ortega but
said the expulsion "came at the wrong time."
</P>
<P>
He added, "The match against England tired us considerably and we
had less than one day to rest, but we are not making excuses.
</P>
<P>
"Of course I regret not being able to continue in the competition,
but we did our best. We gave our maximum effort." 
</P>
</TEXT>
